# 🎓 NotifyCentral: Teacher User Guide

Welcome to **NotifyCentral**! This platform is designed to streamline communication between you and your students, making it easier than ever to share resources, post assignments, and manage your classrooms in one centralized location.

This guide will walk you through everything you need to know to get started.

---

## 🚀 1. Getting Started: Creating Your Account

Before you can manage classrooms, you need to create a Teacher account.

1. Navigate to the **NotifyCentral website**.
2. Click on the **Create Free Account** button on the home page.
3. Fill out your Name, Email, and a secure Password.
4. **Crucial Step:** Under the **Account Role** dropdown, ensure you select **Teacher (Can manage classrooms)**.
5. Click **Register Account**.

> [!CAUTION]
> If you accidentally register as a "Student," you will not be able to create classrooms or assignments. Ensure you select the "Teacher" role during sign-up!

---

## 🏫 2. Creating a Classroom

Once logged in, you will be directed to your Dashboard. To start organizing your students, you'll need to create a Classroom.

1. Navigate to the **Classrooms** tab on the left-hand navigation menu.
2. Click the **Create Classroom** button in the top right corner.
3. Fill in the details:
   - **Classroom Name**: (e.g., *Data Structures & Algorithms - CS301*)
   - **Branch**: (e.g., *CS*)
   - **Year**: Select the applicable year (e.g., *3*)
4. Click **Create** to initialize your new digital classroom!

---

## 🔗 3. Inviting Students (The Class ID)

Your newly created classroom is private. To let your students join, you need to share your unique **Class ID**.

1. From the Classrooms list, click on your newly created classroom to open it.
2. In the top right corner of the classroom header banner, you will see a small box labeled **Class ID**.
3. **Click on the Class ID box** to instantly copy the ID to your clipboard.
4. Paste this ID in an email or group chat for your students.

> [!TIP]
> Students will use this exact ID in their portal by clicking **Join Classroom** and pasting it in. Once they do, they will automatically be synced to your classroom and see all your materials!

---

## 📚 4. Posting Assignments & Resources

You can easily post homework, reading materials, or general assignments directly to the classroom.

1. Inside your specific Classroom, locate the **Assignments** section.
2. Click the **Add Assignment** button.
3. Provide the details:
   - **Title**: What is the assignment called?
   - **Description**: Provide detailed instructions here.
   - **Due Date**: Select the exact date and time the assignment is due.
   - **Upload PDF (Optional)**: If you have a rubric, reading material, or worksheet, you can attach a PDF file here.
4. Click **Post Assignment**.

> [!NOTE]
> As soon as you post an assignment, it instantly becomes visible to all students who have joined your classroom.

---

## 📝 5. Reviewing Student Submissions

When students complete their work, they will upload their solutions directly to the platform as a PDF.

1. Navigate to the Classroom and click **View Details** on an active assignment.
2. Scroll down to the **Submissions** section.
3. You will see a neat table showing exactly who has submitted their work, their Roll Number, and the exact timestamp of their submission.
4. Click **View PDF** next to a student's name to instantly open their submitted document.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The platform will clearly show if a student's submission is legally "Past Due" based on the deadline you established when creating the assignment.

---

### Need Help?
If you run into any issues or have questions about the platform, please reach out to your college's system administrator or technical representative. Welcome to a more organized academic year!
